<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-04-09T10:44:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-04-09T10:44:00-05:00" n="301" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d301">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">882.5048/260: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Liberia</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Carter</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-04-09T15:00:00-00:44">April 9, 1930—3
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 4:51 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>46. My 45, April 7, 7 p.m. Under Christy’s chairmanship, the Commission
                            has virtually completed its organization; and the plan of procedure it
                            is adopting gives it the broadest scope possible, which is very
                            satisfactory. The Commission is expecting to hold a preliminary hearing
                            for about 2 weeks in Monrovia and will then proceed to work in the
                            field.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Carter</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>